description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for highly motivated individuals to join our staff bank as a Band 3 Occupational Therapy Technical Instructor. The role of the post will be to provide support Trustwide to the occupational Therapy services as and when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful Candidates will provide support to each of the Homesafe teams within Northumbria Healthcare as required up to a maximum 37.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Willingness to undertake relevant NVQ L3 within 6 months of appointment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- At least 2 years experience working within an OT department or healthcare setting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 10th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLeona MillarJob titleHomesafe Team ManagerEmail addressleona.millar@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.ukTelephone number07967813959Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Hopper - Homesafe Team Manager, WGH - 01670 529499&lt;/p&gt;
